content:
Here is the cleaned up text:

Embed a Custom Lightning Web Component, a FlexCard, or an OmniScript in a FlexCard

Create a FlexCard.

Don’t embed the same LWC or component in more than one FlexCard.
Drag a Custom LWC element from the Build panel into the FlexCard.
Specify a component. In the Properties panel, enter or select a component:
Custom LWC	The dropdown includes custom LWCs that you created and custom LWCs that come with OmniStudio.
FlexCard created in OmniStudio Standard	In Winter ’23 or later, identify the child FlexCard you want to embed and find its name on the home page. Ensure that the FlexCard is activated, and then enter its name in the Custom LWC Name field.
OmniScript created in OmniStudio Standard	In Winter ’23 or later, enter omnistudioStandardRuntimeWrapper in the Custom LWC Name field.
Add attributes and their values. Click + Add.
When entering the attribute name, use the HTML attribute format.
For example, to use the recordId property, enter record-id for the attribute name.

When you embed an OmniScript created using OmniStudio Standard, the OmniScript’s type, subtype, and language attributes are always required.

The attribute value can be a merge field, such as {Number}, a supported context variable, such as {Session.number}, or text.
In Summer ’21 or later, for a value that consists of plain text and a merge field, enter a concatenated string. For example, enter a breadcrumb path such as {Parent.parentPath}>{Parent.type}>{Name}.

(Optional) Add conditions for displaying the element.
Preview your FlexCard.
title: Embedding Custom Components in FlexCards
